<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept//EN" "concept.dtd">
<concept id="concept_u4h_lwt_ls">
 <title>Using a Hadoop User</title>
 <conbody>
  <p><indexterm>Hadoop FS origin<indexterm>using a Hadoop user to read from
        HDFS</indexterm></indexterm><ph
        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/HUser-Intro"/> origin to
      read from HDFS. </p>
    <p conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/HUser-ImpProperty"/>
    <p>Note that the origin <ph
        conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/HUser-ConnectUser"
        /><draft-comment author="Loretta">Make sure updates to this topic go into the destination
        version of the file.</draft-comment></p>
  <p>To configure a user in the origin to read from HDFS, perform the following tasks:<ol
        id="ul_mb1_xpt_ls">
        <li conref="../Reusable_Content/ReusablePhrases.dita#concept_vhs_5tz_xp/HUser-Step1"/>
        <li>In the Hadoop FS origin, on the <wintitle>Hadoop FS</wintitle> tab, configure the
            <uicontrol>Hadoop FS User</uicontrol> property.</li>
      </ol></p>
 </conbody>
</concept>
